==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From the words '''Serbian''' (''Serbo'' when used as a prefix) and '''Croatian'''.
===Noun===
'''Serbo-Croatian'''

# the [[Serbian]] and [[Croatian]] languages considered as a unit during the existence of [[Yugoslavia]].  Today, the term is used when talking about [[Bosnian]], Croatian, and Serbian languages at the same time or when something being discussed applies to all three languages.

